'''Sloppy seconds''' (or '''slops''' in Australian slang<ref>{{cite book |title=The New Partridge Dictionary of Slang and Unconventional English |editor1-first=Tom |editor1-last=Dalzell |editor2-first=Terry |editor2-last=Victor |year=2013 |edition=2nd |publisher=Routledge |location=Abingdon, Oxon |isbn=978-0-415-61949-3 |page= |url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=abYBCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT17346 }}</ref>) is a slang phrase for when a man has [[sexual intercourse]] with a female or male<ref name="Baker2004">{{cite book|author=Paul Baker|title=Fantabulosa: A Dictionary of Polari and Gay Slang|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=T72TJfZoywAC&pg=PA239|date=25 May 2004|publisher=Bloomsbury Academic|isbn=978-0-8264-7343-1|page=194}}</ref> partner who already has received another man's penis in the relevant orifice and is therefore wet or "sloppy".<ref>{{cite book | last = Doyle | first = Charles | title = The Dictionary of Modern Proverbs | publisher = Yale University Press | location = New Haven | year = 2012 | isbn = 0300136021 | page = 234 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Congressional Record|page = 16928 | date =July 23, 1998}} Original source: "Where'd you learn that?", article in ''Time'' magazine, Monday, June 15, 1998.</ref> The phrase ''buttered bun'' is sometimes used to refer to said orifice.<ref>{{cite book | last = Comfort | first = Alex | title = The Joy of Sex: a Cordon Bleu guide to lovemaking | publisher = Pocket Books | location = New York | year = 1987 | isbn = 0671735187 | page = 160}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Grose | first = Francis | last2 = Partridge | first2 = Eric | title = A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue | publisher = Beard Books | location = Washington, D.C., United States | year = 2004 | isbn = 1587982471 | page = 63}}</ref> The practice is also referred to as a "wet deck".<ref>Edwin Benzel Steen and James Harold Price, ''Human Sex and Sexuality'' (1988), p. 332.</ref>

The term is used, by extension, to refer to any act of entering into a sexual relationship with a person who had previously been in a sexual relationship with someone else in one's peer group.<ref>Luisa Dillner, ''Love by Numbers: The Hidden Facts Behind Everyone's Relationships'' (2009), p. 47.</ref>

There is considerable debate is to why exactly the seconds are sloppy. The most currently accepted theory is that it is the [[Semen|cum]], however there remains some disagreement and this remains an open area of research as of 2018.

